                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d670">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.3516/8–2648: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Dairen</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Paddock</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-08-26T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 26, 1948—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>51. Closing post Vladivostok<note n="2" xml:id="d670fn2">For situation leading to
                        the closing of the Consulate General at Vladivostok, see note 156 from the
                        Soviet Embassy, August 24, and the Department of State’s note, September 9,
                            <ref target="frus1948v04">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>
                        </ref>, “Union of Soviet Socialist Republics” (collection 3).</note> will
                    require transmitting messages Dept thru Emb Moscow. Attempt send next tel both
                    routes as test. Emb Moscow advised.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
